{
  "video_id": "6wNif5SlN08",
  "title": "Don't feel sorry for refugees -- believe in them | Luma Mufleh",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12764.0,
      "end_time": 14661.0,
      "text": "I remember when I first found out"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14686.0,
      "end_time": 16725.0,
      "text": "I was going to speak at a TED conference."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16749.0,
      "end_time": 18860.0,
      "text": "I ran across the hall to one of my classrooms"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18884.0,
      "end_time": 20313.0,
      "text": "to inform my students."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 20337.0,
      "end_time": 21585.0,
      "text": "\"Guess what, guys?"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 21609.0,
      "end_time": 23687.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve been asked to give a TED Talk.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 23711.0,
      "end_time": 25741.0,
      "text": "The reaction wasn&#39;t one I quite expected."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 25766.0,
      "end_time": 27223.0,
      "text": "The whole room went silent."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 28954.0,
      "end_time": 31914.0,
      "text": "\"A TED Talk? You mean, like the one you made us watch on grit?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 31938.0,
      "end_time": 35632.0,
      "text": "Or the one with the scientist that did this really awesome thing with robots?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 35657.0,
      "end_time": 36822.0,
      "text": "Muhammad asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 36847.0,
      "end_time": 38268.0,
      "text": "\"Yes, just like that.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 38957.0,
      "end_time": 41891.0,
      "text": "\"But Coach, those people are really important and smart.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 41915.0,
      "end_time": 43992.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 44160.0,
      "end_time": 45338.0,
      "text": "\"I know that.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 46613.0,
      "end_time": 50330.0,
      "text": "\"But Coach, why are you speaking? You hate public speaking.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 50891.0,
      "end_time": 52400.0,
      "text": "\"I do,\" I admitted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 54154.0,
      "end_time": 57753.0,
      "text": "\"But it&#39;s important that I speak about us, that I speak about your journeys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57777.0,
      "end_time": 58936.0,
      "text": "about my journey."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 58960.0,
      "end_time": 60229.0,
      "text": "People need to know.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 60918.0,
      "end_time": 63631.0,
      "text": "The students at the all-refugee school that I founded"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 63655.0,
      "end_time": 66470.0,
      "text": "decided to end with some words of encouragement."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 66710.0,
      "end_time": 67890.0,
      "text": "\"Cool! It better be good, Coach.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 67914.0,
      "end_time": 70614.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 70638.0,
      "end_time": 74196.0,
      "text": "There are 65.3 million people who have been forcibly displaced"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 74220.0,
      "end_time": 76768.0,
      "text": "from their homes because of war or persecution."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 77855.0,
      "end_time": 80838.0,
      "text": "The largest number, 11 million, are from Syria."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 81783.0,
      "end_time": 86142.0,
      "text": "33,952 people flee their homes daily."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 88666.0,
      "end_time": 91863.0,
      "text": "The vast majority remain in refugee camps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 91888.0,
      "end_time": 95913.0,
      "text": "whose conditions cannot be defined as humane under anyone&#39;s definition."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 96506.0,
      "end_time": 100856.0,
      "text": "We are participating in the degradation of humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 104570.0,
      "end_time": 106351.0,
      "text": "Never have we had numbers this high."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 106375.0,
      "end_time": 109496.0,
      "text": "This is the highest number of refugees since World War II."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110235.0,
      "end_time": 113700.0,
      "text": "Now, let me tell you why this issue is so important to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113964.0,
      "end_time": 116714.0,
      "text": "I am an Arab. I am an immigrant."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 117844.0,
      "end_time": 119110.0,
      "text": "I am a Muslim."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 119826.0,
      "end_time": 123600.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve also spent the last 12 years of my life working with refugees."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 123624.0,
      "end_time": 125650.0,
      "text": "Oh -- and I&#39;m also gay."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 125900.0,
      "end_time": 126990.0,
      "text": "It makes me really popular these days."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 127140.0,
      "end_time": 128905.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 128929.0,
      "end_time": 130872.0,
      "text": "But I am the daughter of a refugee."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 131876.0,
      "end_time": 136374.0,
      "text": "My grandmother fled Syria in 1964 during the first Assad regime."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 136398.0,
      "end_time": 139845.0,
      "text": "She was three months pregnant when she packed up a suitcase,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 139869.0,
      "end_time": 142963.0,
      "text": "piled in her five children and drove to neighboring Jordan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 142987.0,
      "end_time": 145999.0,
      "text": "not knowing what the future held for her and her family."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 146230.0,
      "end_time": 149660.0,
      "text": "My grandfather decided to stay, not believing it was that bad."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 150382.0,
      "end_time": 153856.0,
      "text": "He followed her a month later, after his brothers were tortured"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153880.0,
      "end_time": 156309.0,
      "text": "and his factory was taken over by the government."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 156859.0,
      "end_time": 159530.0,
      "text": "They rebuilt their lives starting from scratch"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 159770.0,
      "end_time": 162352.0,
      "text": "and eventually became independently wealthy Jordanian citizens."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 163789.0,
      "end_time": 166281.0,
      "text": "I was born in Jordan 11 years later."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 167251.0,
      "end_time": 170561.0,
      "text": "It was really important to my grandmother for us to know our history"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 170585.0,
      "end_time": 171739.0,
      "text": "and our journey."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 172703.0,
      "end_time": 176320.0,
      "text": "I was eight years old when she took me to visit my first refugee camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 176344.0,
      "end_time": 177784.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t understand why."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 178456.0,
      "end_time": 180587.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t know why it was so important to her"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 180611.0,
      "end_time": 182600.0,
      "text": "for us to go."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 182850.0,
      "end_time": 185240.0,
      "text": "I remember walking into the camp holding her hand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 185480.0,
      "end_time": 187170.0,
      "text": "and her saying, \"Go play with the kids,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 187410.0,
      "end_time": 189543.0,
      "text": "while she visited with the women in the camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 190426.0,
      "end_time": 191637.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t want to."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 191662.0,
      "end_time": 193780.0,
      "text": "These kids weren&#39;t like me."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 193102.0,
      "end_time": 194880.0,
      "text": "They were poor. They lived in a camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 194904.0,
      "end_time": 196244.0,
      "text": "I refused."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 196268.0,
      "end_time": 199234.0,
      "text": "She knelt down beside me and firmly said, \"Go."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 199258.0,
      "end_time": 201412.0,
      "text": "And don&#39;t come back until you&#39;ve played."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 201436.0,
      "end_time": 203476.0,
      "text": "Don&#39;t ever think people are beneath you"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 203500.0,
      "end_time": 205799.0,
      "text": "or that you have nothing to learn from others.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 206340.0,
      "end_time": 207789.0,
      "text": "I reluctantly went."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 207813.0,
      "end_time": 210101.0,
      "text": "I never wanted to disappoint my grandmother."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 211295.0,
      "end_time": 212691.0,
      "text": "I returned a few hours later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 212716.0,
      "end_time": 217346.0,
      "text": "having spent some time playing soccer with the kids in the camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 217859.0,
      "end_time": 219136.0,
      "text": "We walked out of the camp,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 219160.0,
      "end_time": 221855.0,
      "text": "and I was excitedly telling her what a great time I had"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 221879.0,
      "end_time": 223810.0,
      "text": "and how fantastic the kids were."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 224995.0,
      "end_time": 227675.0,
      "text": "\"Haram!\" I said in Arabic. \"Poor them.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 228468.0,
      "end_time": 231554.0,
      "text": "\"Haram on us,\" she said, using the word&#39;s different meaning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 231579.0,
      "end_time": 232912.0,
      "text": "that we were sinning."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 233822.0,
      "end_time": 236195.0,
      "text": "\"Don&#39;t feel sorry for them; believe in them.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 238171.0,
      "end_time": 241590.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t until I left my country of origin for the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 241614.0,
      "end_time": 243626.0,
      "text": "that I realized the impact of her words."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 245700.0,
      "end_time": 248681.0,
      "text": "After my college graduation, I applied for and was granted political asylum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 248705.0,
      "end_time": 250797.0,
      "text": "based on being a member of a social group."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 251530.0,
      "end_time": 253220.0,
      "text": "Some people may not realize this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 253244.0,
      "end_time": 256910.0,
      "text": "but you can still get the death penalty in some countries for being gay."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 258897.0,
      "end_time": 260940.0,
      "text": "I had to give up my Jordanian citizenship."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 260964.0,
      "end_time": 263414.0,
      "text": "That was the hardest decision I&#39;ve ever had to make,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 263438.0,
      "end_time": 264818.0,
      "text": "but I had no other choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 269207.0,
      "end_time": 270450.0,
      "text": "The point is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 271326.0,
      "end_time": 274402.0,
      "text": "when you find yourself choosing between home and survival,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 274426.0,
      "end_time": 277258.0,
      "text": "the question \"Where are you from?\" becomes very loaded."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 278592.0,
      "end_time": 281859.0,
      "text": "A Syrian woman who I recently met at a refugee camp in Greece"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 281883.0,
      "end_time": 283150.0,
      "text": "articulated it best,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 283175.0,
      "end_time": 286745.0,
      "text": "when she recalled the exact moment she realized she had to flee Aleppo."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 287970.0,
      "end_time": 289354.0,
      "text": "\"I looked out the window and there was nothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 289379.0,
      "end_time": 290738.0,
      "text": "It was all rubble."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 291413.0,
      "end_time": 295205.0,
      "text": "There were no stores, no streets, no schools. Everything was gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 295826.0,
      "end_time": 297873.0,
      "text": "I had been in my apartment for months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 297897.0,
      "end_time": 300967.0,
      "text": "listening to bombs drop and watching people die."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 301591.0,
      "end_time": 303654.0,
      "text": "But I always thought it would get better,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 304848.0,
      "end_time": 306922.0,
      "text": "that no one could force me to leave,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 306946.0,
      "end_time": 308988.0,
      "text": "no one could take my home away from me."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 309615.0,
      "end_time": 312887.0,
      "text": "And I don&#39;t know why it was that morning, but when I looked outside,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 312911.0,
      "end_time": 316490.0,
      "text": "I realized if I didn&#39;t leave, my three young children would die."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 316730.0,
      "end_time": 317462.0,
      "text": "And so we left."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 317486.0,
      "end_time": 320490.0,
      "text": "We left because we had to, not because we wanted to."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 320514.0,
      "end_time": 322262.0,
      "text": "There was no choice,\" she said."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 323798.0,
      "end_time": 326760.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s kind of hard to believe that you belong"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 326100.0,
      "end_time": 327564.0,
      "text": "when you don&#39;t have a home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 327588.0,
      "end_time": 331594.0,
      "text": "when your country of origin rejects you because of fear or persecution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 331618.0,
      "end_time": 335522.0,
      "text": "or the city that you grew up in is completely destroyed."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 336625.0,
      "end_time": 338656.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t feel like I had a home."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 338680.0,
      "end_time": 341137.0,
      "text": "I was no longer a Jordanian citizen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 341161.0,
      "end_time": 342793.0,
      "text": "but I wasn&#39;t American, either."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 343463.0,
      "end_time": 345201.0,
      "text": "I felt a kind of loneliness"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 345225.0,
      "end_time": 347344.0,
      "text": "that is still hard to put into words today."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 348601.0,
      "end_time": 351884.0,
      "text": "After college, I desperately needed to find a place to call home."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 352366.0,
      "end_time": 354820.0,
      "text": "I bounced around from state to state"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 354106.0,
      "end_time": 356541.0,
      "text": "and eventually ended up in North Carolina."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 356565.0,
      "end_time": 358690.0,
      "text": "Kindhearted people who felt sorry for me"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 359233.0,
      "end_time": 360567.0,
      "text": "offered to pay rent"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 361225.0,
      "end_time": 364539.0,
      "text": "or buy me a meal or a suit for my new interview."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 364563.0,
      "end_time": 367586.0,
      "text": "It just made me feel more isolated and incapable."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 368301.0,
      "end_time": 370115.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t until I met Miss Sarah,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 370139.0,
      "end_time": 373875.0,
      "text": "a Southern Baptist who took me in at my lowest and gave me a job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 373899.0,
      "end_time": 375792.0,
      "text": "that I started to believe in myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 376515.0,
      "end_time": 380312.0,
      "text": "Miss Sarah owned a diner in the mountains of North Carolina."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 381676.0,
      "end_time": 383844.0,
      "text": "I assumed, because of my privileged upbringing"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 383869.0,
      "end_time": 385388.0,
      "text": "and my Seven Sister education,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 385412.0,
      "end_time": 387616.0,
      "text": "that she would ask me to manage the restaurant."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 387640.0,
      "end_time": 388848.0,
      "text": "I was wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 389792.0,
      "end_time": 391494.0,
      "text": "I started off washing dishes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 391519.0,
      "end_time": 393498.0,
      "text": "cleaning toilets and working the grill."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 394670.0,
      "end_time": 397152.0,
      "text": "I was humbled; I was shown the value of hard work."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 397176.0,
      "end_time": 399786.0,
      "text": "But most importantly, I felt valued and embraced."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 400744.0,
      "end_time": 402624.0,
      "text": "I celebrated Christmas with her family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 402648.0,
      "end_time": 405000.0,
      "text": "and she attempted to observe Ramadan with me."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 406560.0,
      "end_time": 408726.0,
      "text": "I remember being very nervous about coming out to her --"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 408750.0,
      "end_time": 410792.0,
      "text": "after all, she was a Southern Baptist."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 410816.0,
      "end_time": 412275.0,
      "text": "I sat on the couch next to her"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 412300.0,
      "end_time": 414831.0,
      "text": "and I said, \"Miss Sarah, you know that I&#39;m gay.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 414855.0,
      "end_time": 417410.0,
      "text": "Her response is one that I will never forget."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 417535.0,
      "end_time": 419734.0,
      "text": "\"That&#39;s fine, honey. Just don&#39;t be a slut.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 419758.0,
      "end_time": 422930.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 422954.0,
      "end_time": 425629.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 425653.0,
      "end_time": 431565.0,
      "text": "I eventually moved to Atlanta, still trying to find my home."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 432810.0,
      "end_time": 434460.0,
      "text": "My journey took a strange turn three years later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 434484.0,
      "end_time": 437717.0,
      "text": "after I met a group of refugee kids playing soccer outside."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 438138.0,
      "end_time": 440678.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d made a wrong turn into this apartment complex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 440702.0,
      "end_time": 442917.0,
      "text": "and I saw these kids outside playing soccer."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 443316.0,
      "end_time": 445878.0,
      "text": "They were playing barefoot with a raggedy soccer ball"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 445903.0,
      "end_time": 447355.0,
      "text": "and rocks set up as goals."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 447379.0,
      "end_time": 449790.0,
      "text": "I watched them for about an hour,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 449103.0,
      "end_time": 450681.0,
      "text": "and after that I was smiling."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 451116.0,
      "end_time": 452703.0,
      "text": "The boys reminded me of home."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 453188.0,
      "end_time": 455666.0,
      "text": "They reminded me of the way I grew up playing soccer"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 455690.0,
      "end_time": 458320.0,
      "text": "in the streets of Jordan, with my brothers and cousins."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 459612.0,
      "end_time": 461613.0,
      "text": "I eventually joined their game."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 461637.0,
      "end_time": 464480.0,
      "text": "They were a little skeptical about letting me join it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 464504.0,
      "end_time": 467166.0,
      "text": "because according to them, girls don&#39;t know how to play."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 467190.0,
      "end_time": 468536.0,
      "text": "But obviously I did."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 468560.0,
      "end_time": 470804.0,
      "text": "I asked them if they had ever played on a team."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 470828.0,
      "end_time": 473262.0,
      "text": "They said they hadn&#39;t, but that they would love to."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 473751.0,
      "end_time": 476772.0,
      "text": "I gradually won them over, and we formed our first team."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 477671.0,
      "end_time": 482555.0,
      "text": "This group of kids would give me a crash course in refugees, poverty"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 483817.0,
      "end_time": 485490.0,
      "text": "and humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 486195.0,
      "end_time": 489750.0,
      "text": "Three brothers from Afghanistan -- Roohullah, Noorullah and Zabiullah --"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 489774.0,
      "end_time": 491398.0,
      "text": "played a major role in that."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 492200.0,
      "end_time": 495768.0,
      "text": "I showed up late to practice one day to find the field completely deserted."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 495792.0,
      "end_time": 496972.0,
      "text": "I was really worried."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 496997.0,
      "end_time": 498608.0,
      "text": "My team loved to practice."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 498632.0,
      "end_time": 501239.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t like them to miss practice."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 501263.0,
      "end_time": 504351.0,
      "text": "I got out of my car, and two kids ran out from behind a dumpster,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 504375.0,
      "end_time": 505958.0,
      "text": "waving their hands frantically."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 506915.0,
      "end_time": 508962.0,
      "text": "\"Coach, Rooh got beat up. He got jumped."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 508986.0,
      "end_time": 510563.0,
      "text": "There was blood everywhere.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 510588.0,
      "end_time": 513430.0,
      "text": "\"What do you mean? What do you mean he got beat up?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 513669.99999999994,
      "end_time": 515139.99999999994,
      "text": "\"These bad kids came and beat him up, Coach."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 515164.0,
      "end_time": 517390.0,
      "text": "Everybody left. They were all scared.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 517414.0,
      "end_time": 520131.0,
      "text": "We hopped into my car and drove over to Rooh&#39;s apartment."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 520155.0,
      "end_time": 522655.0,
      "text": "I knocked on the door, and Noor opened it."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 523409.0,
      "end_time": 526161.0,
      "text": "\"Where&#39;s Rooh? I need to talk to him, see if he&#39;s OK.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 526185.0,
      "end_time": 529121.0,
      "text": "\"He&#39;s in his room, Coach. He&#39;s refusing to come out.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 529145.0,
      "end_time": 530312.0,
      "text": "I knocked on the door."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 530336.0,
      "end_time": 532762.0,
      "text": "\"Rooh, come on out. I need to talk to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 532786.0,
      "end_time": 535837.0,
      "text": "I need to see if you&#39;re OK or if we need to go to the hospital.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 535861.0,
      "end_time": 537120.0,
      "text": "He came out."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 537360.0,
      "end_time": 539297.0,
      "text": "He had a big gash on his head, a split lip,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 539839.0,
      "end_time": 541590.0,
      "text": "and he was physically shaken."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 542334.0,
      "end_time": 543666.0,
      "text": "I was looking at him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 543691.0,
      "end_time": 546250.0,
      "text": "and I asked the boys to call for their mom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 546274.0,
      "end_time": 548686.0,
      "text": "because I needed to go to the hospital with him."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 548710.0,
      "end_time": 550170.0,
      "text": "They called for their mom."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 550428.0,
      "end_time": 551620.0,
      "text": "She came out."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 552590.0,
      "end_time": 555637.0,
      "text": "I had my back turned to her, and she started screaming in Farsi."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 556397.0,
      "end_time": 558472.0,
      "text": "The boys fell to the ground laughing."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 558496.0,
      "end_time": 559648.0,
      "text": "I was very confused,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 559672.0,
      "end_time": 561746.0,
      "text": "because there was nothing funny about this."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 562210.0,
      "end_time": 564210.0,
      "text": "They explained to me that she said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 564234.0,
      "end_time": 567480.0,
      "text": "\"You told me your coach was a Muslim and a woman.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 567720.0,
      "end_time": 569441.0,
      "text": "From behind, I didn&#39;t appear to be either to her."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 569465.0,
      "end_time": 573980.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 573122.0,
      "end_time": 575358.0,
      "text": "\"I am Muslim,\" I said, turning to her."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 575382.0,
      "end_time": 577313.0,
      "text": "\"Ašhadu ʾan lā ʾilāha ʾilla (A)llāh,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 577337.0,
      "end_time": 579706.0,
      "text": "reciting the Muslim declaration of faith."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 580407.0,
      "end_time": 581711.0,
      "text": "Confused,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 583280.0,
      "end_time": 585180.0,
      "text": "and perhaps maybe a little bit reassured,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 585420.0,
      "end_time": 586197.0,
      "text": "she realized that yes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 586221.0,
      "end_time": 589512.0,
      "text": "I, this American-acting, shorts-wearing, non-veiled woman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 589536.0,
      "end_time": 590726.0,
      "text": "was indeed a Muslim."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 591986.0,
      "end_time": 593936.0,
      "text": "Their family had fled the Taliban."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 595507.0,
      "end_time": 597210.0,
      "text": "Hundreds of people in their village"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 597235.0,
      "end_time": 598481.0,
      "text": "were murdered."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 598505.0,
      "end_time": 600718.0,
      "text": "Their father was taken in by the Taliban,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 600742.0,
      "end_time": 604543.0,
      "text": "only to return a few months later, a shell of the man he once was."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 606558.0,
      "end_time": 608968.0,
      "text": "The family escaped to Pakistan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 608993.0,
      "end_time": 612561.0,
      "text": "and the two older boys, age eight and 10 at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 612585.0,
      "end_time": 615822.0,
      "text": "wove rugs for 10 hours a day to provide for their family."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 616746.0,
      "end_time": 620502.0,
      "text": "They were so excited when they found out that they had been approved"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 620527.0,
      "end_time": 623190.0,
      "text": "to resettle in the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 623430.0,
      "end_time": 626296.0,
      "text": "making them the lucky 0.1 percent who get to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 626320.0,
      "end_time": 627910.0,
      "text": "They had hit the jackpot."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 628750.0,
      "end_time": 630320.0,
      "text": "Their story is not unique."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 630905.0,
      "end_time": 634813.0,
      "text": "Every refugee family I have worked with has had some version of this."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 634837.0,
      "end_time": 636177.0,
      "text": "I work with kids"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 637260.0,
      "end_time": 640885.0,
      "text": "who have seen their mothers raped, their fathers&#39; fingers sliced off."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 640909.0,
      "end_time": 643864.0,
      "text": "One kid saw a bullet put in his grandmother&#39;s head,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 643888.0,
      "end_time": 647926.0,
      "text": "because she refused to let the rebels take him to be a child soldier."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 649763.0,
      "end_time": 651304.0,
      "text": "Their journeys are haunting."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 651760.0,
      "end_time": 657534.0,
      "text": "But what I get to see every day is hope, resilience, determination,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 657558.0,
      "end_time": 658742.0,
      "text": "a love of life"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 658767.0,
      "end_time": 661611.0,
      "text": "and appreciation for being able to rebuild their lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 663427.0,
      "end_time": 665552.0,
      "text": "I was at the boys&#39; apartment one night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 665576.0,
      "end_time": 670386.0,
      "text": "when the mom came home after cleaning 18 hotel rooms in one day."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 670410.0,
      "end_time": 672703.0,
      "text": "She sat down, and Noor rubbed her feet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 673499.0,
      "end_time": 676574.0,
      "text": "saying that he was going to take care of her once he graduated."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 676598.0,
      "end_time": 678920.0,
      "text": "She smiled from exhaustion."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 678116.0,
      "end_time": 681524.0,
      "text": "\"God is good. Life is good. We are lucky to be here.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 682821.0,
      "end_time": 687616.0,
      "text": "In the last two years, we have seen an escalating anti-refugee sentiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 688390.0,
      "end_time": 689258.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s global."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 690399.0,
      "end_time": 693643.0,
      "text": "The numbers continue to grow because we do nothing to prevent it"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 693667.0,
      "end_time": 695368.0,
      "text": "and nothing to stop it."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 695392.0,
      "end_time": 698944.0,
      "text": "The issue shouldn&#39;t be stopping refugees from coming into our countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 698968.0,
      "end_time": 701956.0,
      "text": "The issue should be not forcing them to leave their own."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 701980.0,
      "end_time": 706415.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 718330.0,
      "end_time": 719655.0,
      "text": "Sorry."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 719679.0,
      "end_time": 723607.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 729737.0,
      "end_time": 732262.0,
      "text": "How much more suffering,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 732286.0,
      "end_time": 734330.0,
      "text": "how much more suffering must we take?"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 735750.0,
      "end_time": 737846.0,
      "text": "How many more people need to be forced out of their homes"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 737870.0,
      "end_time": 739251.0,
      "text": "before we say, \"Enough!\"?"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 739275.0,
      "end_time": 740483.0,
      "text": "A hundred million?"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 740945.0,
      "end_time": 743771.0,
      "text": "Not only do we shame, blame and reject them"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 745650.0,
      "end_time": 747898.0,
      "text": "for atrocities that they had absolutely nothing to do with,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 748832.0,
      "end_time": 749987.0,
      "text": "we re-traumatize them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 750110.0,
      "end_time": 752976.0,
      "text": "when we&#39;re supposed to be welcoming them into our countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 755111.0,
      "end_time": 758414.0,
      "text": "We strip them of their dignity and treat them like criminals."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 758438.0,
      "end_time": 761144.0,
      "text": "I had a student in my office a couple of weeks ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 761168.0,
      "end_time": 762984.0,
      "text": "She&#39;s originally from Iraq."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 763800.0,
      "end_time": 764447.0,
      "text": "She broke down crying."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 765415.0,
      "end_time": 767430.0,
      "text": "\"Why do they hate us?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 767670.0,
      "end_time": 768241.0,
      "text": "\"Who hates you?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 768265.0,
      "end_time": 771360.0,
      "text": "\"Everyone; everyone hates us because we are refugees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 771600.0,
      "end_time": 772415.0,
      "text": "because we are Muslim.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 773839.0,
      "end_time": 776175.0,
      "text": "In the past, I was able to reassure my students"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 776199.0,
      "end_time": 778835.0,
      "text": "that the majority of the world does not hate refugees."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 778860.0,
      "end_time": 780245.0,
      "text": "But this time I couldn&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 780688.0,
      "end_time": 784168.0,
      "text": "I couldn&#39;t explain to her why someone tried to rip off her mother&#39;s hijab"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 784192.0,
      "end_time": 785977.0,
      "text": "when they were grocery shopping,"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 786100.0,
      "end_time": 789245.0,
      "text": "or why a player on an opposing team called her a terrorist"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 789269.0,
      "end_time": 791752.0,
      "text": "and told her to go back where she came from."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 791776.0,
      "end_time": 793537.0,
      "text": "I couldn&#39;t reassure her"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 793562.0,
      "end_time": 795901.0,
      "text": "that her father&#39;s ultimate life sacrifice"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 795925.0,
      "end_time": 799450.0,
      "text": "by serving in the United States military as an interpreter"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 799690.0,
      "end_time": 801779.0,
      "text": "would make her more valued as an American citizen."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 802871.0,
      "end_time": 805742.0,
      "text": "We take in so few refugees worldwide."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 806769.0,
      "end_time": 809455.0,
      "text": "We resettle less than 0.1 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 810598.0,
      "end_time": 813798.0,
      "text": "That 0.1 percent benefits us more than them."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 814617.0,
      "end_time": 818402.0,
      "text": "It dumbfounds me how the word \"refugee\" is considered something to be dirty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 818427.0,
      "end_time": 820400.0,
      "text": "something to be ashamed of."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 820640.0,
      "end_time": 821928.0,
      "text": "They have nothing to be ashamed of."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 825647.0,
      "end_time": 828370.0,
      "text": "We have seen advances in every aspect of our lives --"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 828394.0,
      "end_time": 829772.0,
      "text": "except our humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 830343.0,
      "end_time": 834781.0,
      "text": "There are 65.3 million people who have been forced out of their homes"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 834806.0,
      "end_time": 836500.0,
      "text": "because of war --"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 836505.0,
      "end_time": 838354.0,
      "text": "the largest number in history."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 838930.0,
      "end_time": 840987.0,
      "text": "We are the ones who should be ashamed."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 841532.0,
      "end_time": 842687.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 842711.0,
      "end_time": 849240.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}